data.title: Delicious Fresh Brewed Beers on Tap!
data.text: Delicious fresh brewed beers on tap-do I need to say more? OK, so there is a 100 character minimum so I do need to... :)

data.title: Earthy Beer Bar
data.text: A great selection of local and regional brews, from Trippels to Wheat.  The space is down to earth and at times feels a bit "rough and tumble" but that's part of its charm.  It's family-owned and the father shows a refreshing willingness to get into politics and rail against the system.   No food is served but you they allow food to be bought in or delivered.  There's super salty popcorn to whet your beer whistle.

data.title: Craigslist Basement Bar!
data.text: Great place to kill time with free arcade games & popcorn while enjoying a bourbon stout! Friendly service and a laid back atmosphere. Need some cleaning but it's a real beer joint. Nothing foo-foo!

data.title: Great Place for a Beer Close to Steinbeck Center
data.text: We were in Salinas to go to the Steinbeck Center.  This is a couple of minutes walk away from the center.  Its a good place for an end of the day beer.  This is a great craft beer place to go.  Service was good too.

data.title: A rustic pub for serious beer drinkers
data.text: A great hangout for locals looking for excellent choices in draft beer.  No food but beer and a lot of it.  Friendly bartender.  You will find popcorn though.  The Old Rasputin from North Coast Brewing was just excellent!!!!!  Don't miss this one if you are a serious beer drinker.
